Note: ============================================================================
Note: PowerShell Special Constructs
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits `$(` which starts a PowerShell subexpression — embedded
evaluation inside a double-quoted string or used for grouping.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_dollar then emit_left_paren.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_subexpression_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell subexpression $()

    proc emit_dollar with emitter
    proc emit_left_paren with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits `)` closing the subexpression opened by emit_subexpression_start.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_right_paren.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_subexpression_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell subexpression

    proc emit_right_paren with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits `@(` which starts a PowerShell array literal `@(1, 2, 3)`.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_at_sign then emit_left_paren.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_array_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell array @()

    proc emit_at_sign with emitter
    proc emit_left_paren with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits `)` closing the array opened by emit_array_start.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_right_paren.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_array_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell array

    proc emit_right_paren with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits `@{` which starts a PowerShell hashtable literal
`@{key=value; key2=value2}`.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_at_sign then emit_left_brace.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_hashtable_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell hashtable @{}

    proc emit_at_sign with emitter
    proc emit_left_brace with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits `}` closing the hashtable opened by emit_hashtable_start.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_right_brace.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_hashtable_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell hashtable

    proc emit_right_brace with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits `{` which starts a PowerShell script block — an anonymous
block of code passed to cmdlets like ForEach-Object.
